Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.Place the chicken thighs on a baking tray, skinned side-up. Place half a teaspoon of pesto on top of each thigh and wrap in a piece of prosciutto, folding it in so the seam is on the bottom.Roast for 15â€“20 minutes, or until golden brown and cooked through. Serve with new potatoes and green beans.